Set a password for the user if there is not one.

--> In Admin terminal:
winget install Microsoft.OpenSSH.Preview
winget install GNU.Nano
nano C://ProgramData/ssh/sshd_config

Ensure these configs are there:
  PasswordAuthentication yes
  PermitEmptyPasswords no

Comment these lines:
  #Match Group administrators
  #       AuthorizedKeysFile __PROGRAMDATA__/ssh/administrators_authorized_keys

net stop sshd && net start sshd

--> On the client side:
ssh -l "<username>" <address>
mkdir .ssh
cd .ssh
nano authorized_keys
<paste the pub key and save>
nano C://ProgramData/ssh/sshd_config

Ensure these configs are there:
  PasswordAuthentication no
  PermitEmptyPasswords no

exit

--> On the client side, from now on:
ssh -i <Private id file> -l "<username>" <IP>
Or add the server as a host in ~/.ssh/config folder
